    return the escapement in pixels of the specified string as a value, using
    the fonts loaded for the specified font set. The escapement is the
    distance in pixels in the primary draw direction from the drawing origin
    to the origin of the next character to be drawn, assuming that the
    rendering of the next character is not dependent on the supplied string.

    Regardless of the character rendering order, the escapement is always
    positive.

